          "continents": [
            "Africa"
          ],
          "subspeciesCount": 0,
          "description": "A small, plain reed warbler endemic to Rodrigues Island in the Mascarenes, now extinct, known only from sub-fossil bones and historical accounts. It likely occupied reed beds and scrub along the island's watercourses before habitat destruction and introduced predators (particularly rats and cats) drove it to extinction, probably in the late nineteenth or early twentieth century. Its bones were described in conjunction with the many other Rodrigues extinction-era fauna; it may have survived long enough to be observed by early settlers but was never formally collected.",
