      "description": "Hippolais warblers — medium-sized, active warblers of scrub and garden habitats with loud, complex songs that include mimicry of other species. The icterine warbler (härmsångare) is the most familiar member of the genus in Sweden: a yellow-green bird with a distinctively angular, peaked crown that breeds in parks, gardens, and mixed woodland edge throughout the country. Its song is a rich, tumbling medley of musical phrases, harsh notes, and imitated sounds delivered with great energy from prominent perches — one of the most complex and attractive warbler songs in Sweden. The Swedish name härmsångare ('mimic singer') perfectly captures the bird's talent for weaving snatches of other species' songs into its own performance.",
