          "subspeciesCount": 0,
          "description": "The smallest member of the genus, a delicate, pale warbler of semi-arid scrub, tamarisk and low thorn-bush from Kazakhstan and Central Asia south to northwestern India. Its specific epithet nana refers to its diminutive size. It is an active, tail-flicking species that sings a faint, rapid song from within dense low cover; its song is easily overlooked. The species winters in the Indian subcontinent and is very rarely recorded outside its core Central Asian and South Asian range.",
