            "Africa"
          ],
          "subspeciesCount": 0,
          "description": "A large Iduna of freshwater marshes, reed beds and riverside vegetation in the Middle East, breeding in the marshes of Iraq and Iran and wintering in East Africa. It is one of the least-known members of the family, with limited data on its population size, though it was historically common in the extensive Mesopotamian marshes. The draining of the Iraqi marshes in the 1990s devastated its core breeding habitat, though partial restoration since 2003 has allowed some recovery. Larger and heavier than most congeners.",
